headline: JPMorgan to bring workers back to the office 5 days a week: Rpt.
summary: JPMorgan Chase (JPM) is among the companies looking to intensify its return-to-office policies. According to a Bloomberg report, the banking giant plans to end its hybrid model, requiring staff to return to the office five days per week instead of the current three days allowed. Wealth! co-hosts Seana Smith and Brad Smith break down the decision to enforce in-office work mandates across the banking sector. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Wealth here. This post was written by Angel Smith

headline: JPMorgan becomes latest U.S. lender to quit Net-Zero Banking Alliance
summary: LONDON (Reuters) -JPMorgan said on Tuesday it was leaving the Net-Zero Banking Alliance, the latest U.S. lender to quit the sector's biggest climate coalition amid rising U.S. political pressure.  The move means the six biggest banks in the world's largest economy - Goldman Sachs, Wells Fargo, Citi, Bank of America, Morgan Stanley and now JPMorgan - have all left the group in the space of a month.
